00:43:28,047 --> 00:43:29,674
Did anyone bring my shoes?

801
00:43:29,715 --> 00:43:31,307
Yeah, sure.

802
00:44:19,498 --> 00:44:21,966
Thanks for everything, Arthur.

803
00:44:22,001 --> 00:44:23,059
Thanks a lot.

804
00:44:23,102 --> 00:44:24,729
And I'll be back in the spring.

805
00:44:24,770 --> 00:44:26,362
I'm going to be in shape then;

806
00:44:26,405 --> 00:44:27,895
you'll see.

807
00:44:27,940 --> 00:44:30,568
Yeah, I'll see you then,
and, Bruce...

808
00:44:30,610 --> 00:44:31,975
Yeah.

809
00:44:32,011 --> 00:44:34,980
...see you in Aqua Clara,
all right?

810
00:44:35,014 --> 00:44:36,481
Yeah.

811
00:44:45,324 --> 00:44:48,487
Hey, Arthur, don't forget
to send me a scorecard

812
00:44:48,527 --> 00:44:50,017
from the series, okay?

813
00:44:50,062 --> 00:44:51,393
You bet I will.

814
00:44:51,430 --> 00:44:53,455
Okay.

815
00:44:53,499 --> 00:44:55,194
I'll see you.

816
00:44:58,237 --> 00:44:59,864
I'll see you.

817
00:45:31,704 --> 00:45:33,763
We breezed through the playoffs

818
00:45:33,806 --> 00:45:35,899
and wrapped up the series
on a Sunday.

819
00:45:35,942 --> 00:45:37,341
My win.

820
00:45:37,376 --> 00:45:40,106
I took the scorecard home
and threw it on the shelf

821
00:45:40,146 --> 00:45:42,273
and left it lay there.

822
00:45:42,315 --> 00:45:45,011
It would've been simple
to shove it in the mail.

823
00:45:45,051 --> 00:45:46,848
How long would it have took?

824
00:45:46,886 --> 00:45:49,912
Couldn't I afford the stamps?

825
00:45:49,956 --> 00:45:54,052
In my Arcturis calendar
for December 10, it says:

826
00:45:54,093 --> 00:45:56,653
Desoto visited Georgia, 15-40.

827
00:45:56,696 --> 00:45:58,129
This hands me a laugh.

828
00:45:58,164 --> 00:46:01,065
Bruce Pearson also visited
Georgia.

829
00:46:01,100 --> 00:46:03,534
I was his pallbearer

830
00:46:03,569 --> 00:46:06,129
me and some local boys.

831
00:46:06,172 --> 00:46:08,163
There were flowers
from the club

832
00:46:08,207 --> 00:46:10,072
but no person from the club.

833
00:46:10,109 --> 00:46:13,567
They could've sent somebody.

834
00:46:13,612 --> 00:46:16,308
He wasn't a bad fella...

835
00:46:16,349 --> 00:46:19,546
no worse than most
and probably better than some...

836
00:46:19,585 --> 00:46:21,348
and not a bad ballplayer
neither

837
00:46:21,387 --> 00:46:23,184
when they give him
the chance...

838
00:46:23,222 --> 00:46:25,156
when they laid off him
long enough.

839
00:46:25,257 --> 00:46:31,526
From here on in, I rag nobody.

